The synthesized CNDs showed the wavelength dependent PL emission which is known as wavelength-dependence behavior [42] (Fig. 4
                        ). These CNDs showed increased fluorescence at different excitation values ranging from 230 to 290 nm (Fig. 4a). However, it was observed that PL intensity decreases with an increase in wavelength from 300 nm. The maximum PL intensity was observed at 290 nm (Fig. 4a). However, the PL intensity of the CNDs was started decreasing from λ
                        max 300 nm and attained insignificant PL similar to PL observed at 230 nm (Fig. 4b). On other hand, we have studied the effect of pH on the PL of CNDs. To various reactions mixtures, pH was adjusted from pH1 to pH11, showed a decreased PL as pH tends to alkalinity (Fig. 5
                        ).
